vectorData.altText: 3. The _______________ nerve is associated with abduction of the shoulder.
That's right! The axillary nerve innervates the deltoid muscle, the major abductor of shoulder.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Recall that the axillary nerve passes posterior to the surgical neck of the humerus, accompanied by the posterior circumflex humeral artery     . The axillary nerve innervates the deltoid muscle, and the skin overlying the shoulder. 
Describe the motor and sensory deficits characteristic of a lesion of the axillary nerve. Think, then click!

weakness in abduction of the GH joint
sensory signs (pain, dysesthesia) in the skin overlying the shoulder
